    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="657"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17947</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Arredondo</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: I am in receipt of telegraphic
                    instructions from my Government directing me to secure, through the Department
                    under your excellency’s worthy charge, data relative to the number of
                    engagements between American forces in Mexico and Villa bandits, the places
                    where the same have occurred and the <pb facs="0601" n="525" xml:id="pg_525"/>
                    names of the American commanders at the head of such forces. If it will be
                    possible for your excellency to furnish me with the above data, I shall
                    appreciate it sincerely.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Arredondo</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
